Program: Discovery
Title: Friendly fire
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxf7
Last Broadcast Date: 11 June 1999
An examination of the various incidences of friendly fire in warfare. Accidentally shooting or bombing a soldier on the same side one of the most terrible experiences a soldier can experience. But so-called 'friendly fire' affects civilians too in the form of auto immune disorders which involve the body attacking itself, as the programme discovers. Show less